parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sticking Valve/Knob Failure on Magic Chef Stove
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking valve/knob failure can cause the burner to overheat, leading to a potential fire hazard, explosion, or propane leak, which can put the occupants of the motorhome at risk.
symptoms: unable to turn off or down
the plastic on the knob melts
the stove surface becomes extremely hot
the burner cannot be turned off completely
allowing propane to leak into the motorhome.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Door Design and Latch Mechanism Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The door design and latch mechanism failure can cause the door to be sucked outward with tremendous force, creating a great danger to passengers, especially if the door is accidentally opened or the latch mechanism fails.
symptoms: The door vibrates on the top inside half
the door is sucked outward with tremendous force when traveling at high speeds
the door has been replaced multiple times
modifications have been made to reduce wind noise and flutter but the outward sucking pressure remains.
